com.wpruszak.blitzch.lib.interfaces

Interface FileLoader

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    FileLoaderImpl

    public interface FileLoader
    The main file loading interface for IOController to provide an easy interchangeable way of loading files.

    FileLoader provides:

    • Loading file data from absolute path
    • Loading file from absolute path
    • Loading file data from File object
    • Loading a List of FileBean objects from an array of File objects
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    setzo
    See Also:
    IOController, FileSaver, FileLoaderImpl

      • loadDirectory

        List<FileBean> loadDirectory(File[] files,
                             List<FileBean> fileBeanList)
                      throws IOException
        Recursive load all files of a directory into List of FileBean objects, that will contain all of the files data.
        Parameters:
        files - to load data from into FileBean beans
        fileBeanList - list of FileBean objects containing information about our files, this parameter can and should be initially null, cause the list is created after first iteration of the method anyway.
        Returns:
        List of FileBean objects
        Throws:
        IOException - if I/O is corrupted
